properties.headline: Flood Warning issued March 2 at 8:56PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in the Twin Cities has issued a
Flood Warning for the following rivers in Minnesota...

Cottonwood River Above Springfield affecting Brown County.

.Snowmelt has resulted in rises on the Cottonwood River. The river
is expected to reach flood stage by Tuesday evening.

The National Weather Service in the Twin Cities has issued a

* Flood Warning for
the Cottonwood River Above Springfield.
* From Tuesday evening until further notice.
* At 8:30 PM CST Monday, the stage was 20.9 feet.
* Flood stage is 22.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage
tomorrow evening and continue rising to 23.5 feet Monday evening.
Additional rises are possible thereafter.
* Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 23.7
feet on 06/21/1991.
properties.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.
